    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In the 1950s, a proposal to annex Harbor Isle into neighboring Island Park failed, keeping the hamlet independent.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14,
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harbor_Isle%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Harbor Isle sits between Island Park to the east, Hog Island Channel to the west and north, and Wreck Lead Channel to the south.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        16
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harbor_Isle%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "From Harbor Isle’s shoreline you can see the Village of Island Park and the nearby Barnum Island across the water.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
